    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A tab-based single-page application. Each tab corresponds to one IELTS task from the report. This structure segments the content for focused learning, allowing users to easily navigate between different examples without scrolling. The layout for each task is a two-column grid, separating the prompt/visual from the model answer, which is optimal for comparison and study. This is more user-friendly than a linear document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: House Cup: Bar Chart (Chart.js) to compare discrete values across categories/years. Demographics: Line Chart (Chart.js) to show trends over time. Owl Post: HTML/CSS Flexbox diagram to visualize a process flow. Potion Ingredients: Styled HTML table. Ministry Staffing: Pie Chart (Chart.js) to show proportions. Hogwarts Maps: Side-by-side HTML/CSS layouts to compare two states. These choices map the data type from the source to the best interactive visualization method, enhancing understanding. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
